headline: Mid-America Apartment Communities (MAA) Q4 FFO and Revenues Miss Estimates
summary: Mid-America Apartment Communities (MAA) delivered FFO and revenue surprises of -0.45% and 0.48%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2024. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Mid-America Apartment Communities: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The real estate investment trust, based in Germantown, Tennessee, said it had funds from operations of $244 million, or $2.23 per share, in the period. The average estimate of 10 analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of $2.24 per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.
